commitResults.messageTitle: Rename chatbot and add basic greeting and exit
commitResults.messageBody:
The chatbot's name is Duke and so is the main source file name.
The main source file prints out a 'Duke' logo.

It needs to change because,
* the chatbot's name needs to differentiate from other chatbots' names
* just printing the logo does not help achieve the goal of the chatbot
  being a personal assistant which helps the user keep track of various
  things

Let's,
* rename the chatbot to Athena
* rename Duke.java to Athena.java
* delete the chatbot logo
* implement an initial skeletal version (with horizontal lines seperating
  the starting and ending greetings) of the chatbot to greet the user
  and exit

It is done this way because,
* Athena is not a common name choice, hence differentiating it a lot
* for consistency's sake and to prevent potential future bugs
* horizontal lines will make formatting for future code and main body
  content prompts easier and nicer, laying a good foundation for a
  skeleton code
